                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6298: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bonbright</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-28T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 28, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 29—7:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>479. My 478, of today. The Cabinet is now in session. We have been informed from
                    a reliable source that an announcement is expected afterwards to the effect that
                    Yugoslavia will maintain its neutrality but will defend its territory if
                    attacked.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bonbright</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
